origin story

A very unusual card. I find that it's best use is providing additional burst damage in the early/mid game, especially without actually adding strike+ type cards to your deck. 1 copy of consult playbook can function like 4 standard burst damage commons, though you do need to draw it in a timely fashion. The upgrade is really important to get ASAP, so that you have more energy to play the generated tackles (Most tackles cost 2). 1 copy of roll through can also help you take less damage while using this.

As you get into the later stages of the run, it falls off fairly hard, as you don't necessarily want to fill your deck with random tackles during important/long boss and elite fights. You do always have the option of just not playing it, or only playing it when the fight is nearly over to get that little bit of extra burst. Tackles also aren't really a well supported synergy package, so you will usually be more focused on goop/slime minions at that point in the run. This could be a very valuable card in a tackle archetype to increase the density of tackles in your deck, but there just isn't much of a payoff for doing that with slime bosses current set of powers.

It does really well against the act 1 elites, providing tons of cheap burst damage to close out those fights, and will also do well into the hallway fights during the early game. Having 4 energy helps immensely, as it helps you play more of the generated tackles on the same turn you used consult playbook. I would probably buy this from a shop in act 1, but would rarely want to take it as a card reward from an act boss, since your deck probably has enough frontloaded damage by the end of act 1. Runic pyramid can also help you keep the tackles to use later, when you have the energy and block to play them effectively. Also solid with the ninja relics, pen nib, and nunchaku, as it makes lots of cheap attacks for the fight. The beta art is really charming.

For the record, this can generate four 1 cost tackles (that includes the starter card), and four 2 cost tackles. Opening tackles is particularly nice as it's 1 cost (0 with playbook) , and can help all the other tackles deal even more damage with the vulnerable. Spear tackle is great as a 1 cost that becomes a 0 cost and draws 2 cards, flame tackles is theoretically good since it increases the damage of other tackles, and hungry tackle can let you cheaply recycle a lick and hopefully draw a card. I would say that you are relatively happy with 3 of the 8 tackles this can generate. Vicious, combo, forward and the starter card are all not great, and I doubt that flame tackle will be enough scaling to be relevant. 

As for tackle support in slime boss, roll through helps you avoid their drawback, flame tackle and recklessness increase their damage. You also have the shop relic protective gear to negate the drawback. That's a really small amount of support, and none of it really helps these frontloaded damage cards transition more gracefully into the late game, they just let them deal more front-loaded damage or take away the self damage. I would prefer to see something that let them draw cards, or reduced their costs. Notably they don't have a single piece of support at rare, while goop/licks have 5, and potency gets 2 rare pieces of support. Some kind of rare power that lets tackles be more useful in the late game would help their viability (and therefore consult playbooks viability) significantly.
